<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:lang="en" xml:id="form-raisedlowered">
    <teiHeader>
        <fileDesc>
            <titleStmt>
                <title>Raised or lowered characters</title>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
                <respStmt>
                    <resp/>
                    <name/>
                </respStmt>
            </titleStmt>
            <publicationStmt><p/></publicationStmt>
            <sourceDesc><p/></sourceDesc>
        </fileDesc>
    </teiHeader>
    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="content">
                <div type="leiden">
                <cit type="interpretive">
                    <quote>(none)</quote>
                </cit>
                <cit type="diplomatic"><!-- bad visualisation of lines!!!! -->
                    <quote>none</quote>
                </cit>
            </div>
            <div type="explanation">
                <p>Characters written higher than the surrounding text:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <hi rend="superscript">γ</hi> = αβᵞ
                </egXML>
                <p>Characters written lower than the surrounding text:</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <hi rend="subscript">γ</hi> = αβᵧ
                </egXML>
                <p>Character written directly above another character (as opposed to superscript):</p>
                <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <hi rend="stacked">c</hi>
                </egXML>
                <p> but it is not currently handled by stylesheets.</p>
                <p>If it is for an abbreviation or something supposed to be ‘regularised’ in the edition, those characters should appear above or below line only in the diplomatic edition,
                    especially using Athena Ruby; but sometimes they are simply written like this, and should be represented in the editorial interpretation too.</p>
            </div>
            </div>
            <div type="responsibility">
                <listBibl>
                    <bibl>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Alessio Sopracasa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                        <respStmt>
                            <resp>Author</resp>
                            <name>Martina Filosa</name>
                        </respStmt>
                    </bibl>
                </listBibl>
            </div>
            <div type="version">
                <p>SigiDoc version: 1.0</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
